Detailed Description

Parameters used to configure the receive and transmit message objects.

Field Documentation

CAN_Direction CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::direction

Message object direction. For valid values refer to enum CAN_Direction.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::dirMask

Message Direction Mask: Valid values: 1 or 0.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::fifoEOBFlag

Message object is part of FIFO Buffer or not Valid only for RX - Valid values: 1 or 0.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::intEnable

Interrupt Enable : IntPnd will be triggered or not after the successful transmission/reception of a frame Valid values: 1 or 0.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::msgIdentifier

Message Identifier - [28:0] are valid bits.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::msgIdentifierMask

Identifier Mask - [28:0] are valid bits.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::msgValid

Valid or Invalid Message Objects. Valid values: 1 or 0.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::remoteEnable

At the reception of a remote frame, TxRqst is changed or not Valid only for TX - Valid values: 1 or 0.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::uMaskUsed

Use mask (Msk[28:0], MXtd, and MDir) for acceptance filtering or not.

CAN_DCANXidType CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::xIdFlag

Extended IDE Flag : Standard / Extended Identifier. For valid values refer enum CAN_DCANXidType.

uint32_t CAN_DCANMsgObjCfgParams_t::xIdFlagMask

Extended Identifier IDE bit Mask: Valid values: 1 or 0.
